{"id":14880789,"mediaExerciseId":"cd042b18-5dbc-4d39-baef-29ac06c7c182","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612274,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":84,"solutions":[{"id":5908656,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will learn about peer group analysis and the difference of a peer group from an aspirant group.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/7d12127ef8ba1b3b6fef5e078fb299c5/88c2e9bef503bc93d3da0edfa14d7382/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/7d12127ef8ba1b3b6fef5e078fb299c5/88c2e9bef503bc93d3da0edfa14d7382/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Peer group analysis**  is a process of comparing of entities in the\nsame industry or line of business. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/7d12127ef8ba1b3b6fef5e078fb299c5/832c8360b3cc7946420ff6cc22f9d858/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/7d12127ef8ba1b3b6fef5e078fb299c5/832c8360b3cc7946420ff6cc22f9d858/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"As a financial manager, the results of peer group analysis can be used in evaluating the performance of the firm by providing appropriate course of actions in adjusting financial ratios relative to the other same industry and to better analyze the competitive position of the firm.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/7d12127ef8ba1b3b6fef5e07